thread.title: Report: Former Auburn WR Duke Williams punched, injured teammate Xavier Dampeer in bar fight
thread.title_full: Report: Former Auburn WR Duke Williams punched, injured teammate Xavier Dampeer in bar fight | AL.com

author: Wesley Sinor | wsinor@al.com
title: Report: Former Auburn WR Duke Williams punched, injured teammate Xavier Dampeer in bar fight
text:
Auburn reserve center Xavier Dampeer suffered an injured jaw after being punched during a bar fight in Auburn last weekend, according to Alabama News Network .
A source told the network Dampeer was one of four people attacked by former Auburn wide receiver D'haquille "Duke" Williams , who went on a rampage in an Auburn bar after Saturday's win over San Jose State. AL.com could not confirm whether a teammate was involved in the fight.
When asked Tuesday if any other players were involved in the incident, Tigers head coach Gus Malzahn said, "I'm not going to get into any details."
The network reported Dampeer was treated and released from East Alabama Medical Center, according to a hospital worker. When contacted by AL.com, a hospital spokesperson said there was no patient record of Dampeer at the hospital this week.
Auburn did not immediately respond to a request from AL.com seeking comment on the report. Police told AL.com on Wednesday no police report had been filed regarding Williams.
When asked Tuesday whether his offensive line and defensive lines were healthy, Malzahn said, "I think we're OK."
"As far as Carl Lawson, obviously, with him, but everybody else this week is good that we can get some good work in but we can heal some of the guys up," he said. "There's nothing major, to put it that way."
Auburn head coach Gus Malzahn discusses dismissal of D'haquille Williams Auburn head coach Gus Malzahn fields questions from the press about the dismissal of receiver D'haquille Williams from the team Tuesday, Oct. 6, 2015, after practice in Auburn, Ala. (Julie Bennett/jbennett@al.com)
